////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


// Transparent smoke surface hook fragment. Demonstrates a per-material color transform expressed as a hook (not
// a compile-time variant): the base color is square-root transformed and warm-tinted. The cook wraps it with the
// engine pixel-shader authoring + this material's typed .bind to generate the G-buffer pixel shader.
#include "smoke_material_color.slangi"


////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


NwbMeshSurface nwbMaterialSurface(){
    const NwbMeshInstanceData instance = nwbMeshLoadInstance();
    const NwbSmokeSurfaceMaterial surface = nwbMaterialBindLoadSurface(instance);
    const NwbSmokeRuntimeMaterial runtime = nwbMaterialBindLoadRuntime(instance);
    const float4 tinted = surface.base_color * runtime.color_tint;
    const float3 baseColor = nwbSmokeMaterialVertexColor(tinted.rgb);
    // Unified surface contract: this hook DECIDES each consumer's per-pixel output. The refraction INPUTS
    // (ior/thickness/transmission) are the hook's OWN local material constants -- they never leave the hook. From
    // them it computes `transmittance` (the shadow trace's per-hit output, via the engine Fresnel + Beer-Lambert
    // helper) AND `alpha` (the AVBOIT transparent passes' per-pixel opacity), so all of AVBOIT's occupancy,
    // extinction, and accumulate passes use the IDENTICAL shader-decided alpha. The base color stays the rasterized
    // appearance (the G-buffer discards transmittance + alpha). Hardcoded test values; the production path authors
    // them as typed .bind constants. ior 1.5 = glass; thickness drives the Beer-Lambert path; transmission follows
    // the per-cube tint so the opacity matches the base color. The shadow trace supplies inIncidentDirection (the
    // shadow ray); the rasterizer/AVBOIT passes supply a documented dummy (those discard transmittance anyway).
    const float ior = 1.5;
    const float thickness = 0.5;
    const float3 transmission = saturate(baseColor.rgb) * 0.8;
    const float3 transmittance = nwbShadowRefractiveTransmittance(ior, thickness, transmission, inIncidentDirection, inNormal);
    NwbMeshSurface result = nwbMakeMeshSurface(baseColor, inNormal, 0.0, 0.0, transmittance);
    result.alpha = 1.0 - nwbLuminance(transmission);
    return result;
}


////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
